$Id: README 1800 2005-01-28 06:44:44Z btrott $

This is WWW::Blog::Metadata, a class to extract common metadata from
weblogs.

PREREQUISITES

    * Class::ErrorHandler
    * Feed::Find
    * HTML::Parser
    * URI::Fetch
    * Class::Accessor
    * Module::Pluggable::Ordered

INSTALLATION

WWW::Blog::Metadata installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell
is set up, you should just be able to do

    % perl -MCPAN -e 'install WWW::Blog::Metadata'

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

